---
description: Testing conventions, patterns, and structure for the backend test suite
applyTo: "backend/tests/**/*.py"
---



```
backend/tests/
├── conftest.py              # Root fixtures (DB session, engine, app client) — defined ONCE
├── unit/                    # Fast, isolated, no I/O
│   ├── core/                # Entities, VOs, events, errors, interfaces
│   ├── application/         # Services, DTOs, commands, queries, mappers, tasks
│   ├── infrastructure/      # Repositories (mocked session), cache, messaging, auth
│   ├── presentation/        # App factories, middleware, error handlers
│   ├── utils/               # Enums, validators, logger, retry, date, string, crypto
│   └── config/              # Settings, celery config, DI container
├── integration/             # Real DB, real Redis, real infrastructure
├── property/                # Hypothesis property-based tests
├── performance/             # Benchmarks
├── factories/               # Per-entity test data factories
└── utils/                   # assertion_helpers.py, mock_builder.py, fixture_factory.py
```


| Element         | Pattern                                       |
| --------------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| Test files      | 'test_<module_name>.py'                       |
| Test classes    | 'TestClassName' (no 'unittest.TestCase')      |
| Test functions  | 'test_<action>_<scenario>_<expected_outcome>' |

```python
def test_create_user_with_valid_email_returns_user_entity() -> None: ...
def test_authenticate_with_expired_token_raises_auth_error() -> None: ...

def test_user(): ...
def test_1(): ...
```


EVERY source module MUST have corresponding test(s):

| Source                              | Test                                          |
| ----------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| 'core/entities/*'                  | 'unit/core/test_*_entity.py'                  |
| 'core/value_objects/*'             | 'unit/core/test_value_objects.py'             |
| 'core/events/*'                    | 'unit/core/test_events.py'                    |
| 'core/enums/*'                     | 'unit/core/test_enums.py'                     |
| 'core/exceptions/*'               | 'unit/core/test_exceptions.py'                |
| 'core/interfaces/*'               | 'unit/core/test_interfaces.py'                |
| 'application/services/*'          | 'unit/application/test_*_service.py'          |
| 'application/dtos/*'              | 'unit/application/test_*_dto.py'              |
| 'application/mappers/*'           | 'unit/application/test_*_mapper.py'           |
| 'infrastructure/persistence/repos/*' | 'unit/infrastructure/test_*_repository.py'  |
| 'infrastructure/cache/*'          | 'unit/infrastructure/test_*_cache.py'         |
| 'infrastructure/messaging/*'      | 'unit/infrastructure/test_*_event_bus.py'     |
| 'presentation/api/routes/*'       | 'integration/test_api_routes.py'              |
| 'presentation/api/middleware/*'   | 'unit/presentation/test_middleware.py'         |
| 'utils/*'                          | 'unit/utils/test_*.py' (one per util module)  |
| 'config/settings.py'              | 'unit/config/test_settings.py'                |

Target: ≥ 80% line coverage on 'core' + 'application' layers (enforced by 'tox -e coverage-core')


```python
@pytest.mark.unit          # Fast, isolated, no I/O
@pytest.mark.integration   # Real DB or external service
@pytest.mark.property      # Hypothesis property-based
@pytest.mark.performance   # Benchmarks
@pytest.mark.slow          # Takes > 5 seconds
@pytest.mark.smoke         # Critical path — must pass before deploy
```

Configure in 'pyproject.toml':

```toml
[tool.pytest.ini_options]
markers = [
    "unit: Fast, isolated, no I/O",
    "integration: Real adapters and services",
    "property: Hypothesis property-based",
    "performance: Benchmarks",
    "slow: Tests > 5 seconds",
    "smoke: Critical path",
]
```


- ALL test functions: '-> None' return type
- ALL tests: AAA pattern (Arrange, Act, Assert) — blank line between each
- ALL async tests: 'pytest-asyncio' correctly configured
- ZERO 'print()' — use 'capsys' or assertions
- ZERO 'time.sleep' — mock or async wait
- Edge cases: empty inputs, 'None', boundary values, invalid types
- Exception paths: 'pytest.raises(ExcType, match=...)' with match verification
- '*' enforcement: tests confirming positional usage raises 'TypeError'


- 'conftest.py': 'async_session', 'async_engine', 'test_client' — defined ONCE at root
- '@pytest.fixture' with explicit scope ('function' default, 'session' for DB engine)
- Fixture names describe what they return: 'active_user', 'expired_token'
- Database fixtures transactional (rollback after each test)
- Prefer 'factory_boy' factories over raw fixture data


- Mock at the boundary (interfaces), NEVER inside core
- Prefer dependency injection over monkey-patching
- Never mock what you don't own — wrap external libraries first
- ZERO real DB/Redis in unit tests


```python
from hypothesis import given, strategies as st

@given(st.sampled_from(MyEnum))
def test_enum_round_trip(member: MyEnum) -> None:
    assert MyEnum(member.value) == member
```

- 'tests/property/test_value_objects.py': strategies for all VOs
- '@given(st.sampled_from(MyEnum))' for enum-typed inputs
- Configure 'max_examples' and 'deadline' for CI
- Test invariants (idempotency, round-trips, commutativity), not single examples


- 'tests/utils/assertion_helpers.py': 'assert_domain_error()', custom helpers
- 'tests/utils/mock_builder.py': 'build_mock_repository()', 'build_mock_cache()'
- 'tests/utils/fixture_factory.py': 'build_entity_fixture()' with defaults + overrides
- 'tests/factories/': per-entity test data factories


- Remove tests testing framework behavior (not your code)
- Remove tests only testing mock configuration
- Remove tests with no assertions
- Fix tests passing for wrong reasons (swallowed exceptions)
- Fix order-dependent tests
- Fix tests sharing mutable state
